1.title: Glow Messy
1.plot: When the OKIDO lighthouse breaks down, Messy, Felix, Zoe and Zoom go on an perilous journey through Mystery Mountain in search of a light that never goes out.

2.title: Vote OKIDO
2.plot: Mayor Oki and Geoffrey are making a lot of noise in an election for who will be the next Mayor of OKIDO.

5.title: Messy Has a Hoot
5.plot: Messy and his friends go on a camping trip in OKIDO Forest with Tweedie the Explorer and meet a few more nocturnal animals than they bargained for.

6.title: Sparkly Messy
6.plot: Messy and his friends discover an amazing cave on their quest for the perfect sculpture material for OKIDO's most famous artist, Zinnie.

8.title: Messy Migration
8.plot: When a little turtle gets stranded on the beach in OKIDO, Messy helps her rejoin her friends so they can begin their very important journey across the ocean.

11.title: Nimby Goes to Cloud Club
11.plot: Nimby is too nervous to do his first Cloud Club badge. Messy and friends come up with a plan to help Nimby overcome his nerves and save OKIDO from some mysterious accidents.

12.title: A Touch of the Fogs
12.plot: Everyone in OKIDO is getting ready to watch the dolphin's dance at Vivienne Volcano's island. But why is the island covered in cloud and will Messy and his friends be able to help clear it before the show starts?

13.title: Geoffrey Kneads a Hand
13.plot: A spot of baking with Geoffrey goes awry when Messy gets the quantities wrong. Will the friends escape from the giant dough spreading throughout OKIDO?

14.title: A Mayor Too Far
14.plot: Zam's latest OKIDO invention, hundreds of strawberries and a lot of Mayors help Messy find out what makes him who he is.

15.title: Blue Skies Ahead
15.plot: Why has the sky in OKIDO turned so red? With the help of Zim, Zam and Zoom the friends go on a trip in the rocket to find out.

16.title: Sweet Sticky Messy
16.plot: Mayor Oki creates a new perfume that everyone in OKIDO adores. But what are the bees so upset about?

17.title: Messy Moves A Mountain
17.plot: Rocky Mountain is feeling down in the dumps because he's never been to the beach, so Messy and his friends from OKIDO come up with a clever plan to cheer him up.

18.title: Carroty Carrots
18.plot: Messy and his friends help Lofty the giant make the biggest birthday cake ever but will they ever stop the out of control Growbot? And where did all those carrots all over OKIDO come from?

19.title: Bubble Trouble
19.plot: Bubbles, bubbles, all over OKIDO. Zam invents a super strong bubble machine but things go a bit wrong and Zim finds himself in a spot of bother.

20.title: Supersonic Messy
20.plot: Okidoodle is jealous of the new RoboCar, which can go super fast. Will Okidoodle be able to catch up with RoboCar and earn Messy's admiration back? It's time to use the turbo button for a supersonic trip around OKIDO City to find out. Balabalaboomboom.

21.title: Muscly Messy
21.plot: At the OKIDO Oki-lympics everyone's joining in. A race between Messy with his super muscles and Zam's new amazing robot pants brings up some surprises.

22.title: Messy Mega Power
22.plot: The Oki-dokis are about to perform when OKIDO runs out of electricity. Anxious that their favourite band is not going to be able to play, will Messy and his friends find a new way of powering the concert?

1.title: Moon Landing
1.plot: Why do things always fall down? When you need to know go to OKIDO.

2.title: Felix Finds His Voice
2.plot: Messy hears a bird singing outside but doesn't know what he's trying to say. Maybe he'll find the answer in OKIDO.

3.title: Okido in Bloom
3.plot: The sky is full of big grey rain clouds in the real world. Messy watches his sandcastle outside get washed away by the pouring rain. Why does it have to rain? He competes in the Okido flower competition and finds out why.

4.title: Taste
4.plot: Messy wonders why his tasty green socks don't taste the same when he has a cold.

5.title: Messy's Lost Balloon
5.plot: Messy, Zoe and Felix travel to the land of balloons.

6.title: Float or Sink
6.plot: Why do some things float and some things sink? Pirate Captain Messy will find out in Okido.

7.title: Bouncing Batwaves
7.plot: Messy is having fun blowing loud notes through his musical horn instrument "PARP PARP!!" But whatever noise Messy is making someone or something is making it too. Messy goes in search of the copycat voice.

8.title: Cavity Cave
8.plot: Why do we need to brush our teeth? When you need to now go to Okido.

10.title: Messy-Morphosis
10.plot: Messy wants to know where his caterpillar friends went.

11.title: Thirsty Robot
11.plot: Messy monster can't work out why his cart won't move. The wheels just won't go round like normal. Off he goes to Okido to find out why.

12.title: Mr Kite Takes Flight
12.plot: Messy monster is just about to take a bite out of his delicious green sock for breakfast but before he can... WHOOOSH! His sock has blown away! He goes to Okido to find out why the wind is so blowy!

13.title: Weepy
13.plot: Messy finds a very dusty sock underneath his bed but why does it make him teary? He goes to Okido to find out.

14.title: Gills
14.plot: Messy wants to know how his goldfish friend can stay underwater for so long? He goes to Okido to find out.

15.title: Paperchase
15.plot: Messy has a pair of yummy green socks waiting for him. He eats one but where is the second? In Okido he finds out.

16.title: Lolly's Keys
16.plot: Messy monster is having breakfast and sees little objects on the fridge, why don't they fall off? He goes to Okido to find out.

17.title: Ice Ice Messy
17.plot: Messy's new friend is in a spot of hot bother. They go on an icy adventure to the south pole, the desert and mountains to help.

18.title: A Messy Night Before Christmas
18.plot: Messy can't wait for Christmas Day to arrive. He learns that everyone needs to get a good night's sleep, even Mother Christmas.

19.title: A Night at the Circuits
19.plot: Messy joins his friends in Okido on a tiny adventure. They explore the electrical world of circuits to fix Zoe's communicator.

20.title: Messy-Power
20.plot: Hey, who turned out the lights? Messy goes to Okido and finds out electricity can lead to music, lights and disco dancing.

21.title: Planet Wobble
21.plot: Messy and friends rocket into space but a mischievous Messy sends Okido's seasons into chaos. Time to fix this planet wobble.

22.title: Alien Television
22.plot: Aliens on Okido telly? Skateboarders in the satellite?. Everything's upside down. It's up to Messy and his friends to fix it.

23.title: Comet
23.plot: Messy has to save Okido from a falling comet before his bedtime. He sees that Mayor Oki still has his bath.

24.title: Bee Story
24.plot: There's some funny 'buzzy-ness' going on in Okido. Where are all the bees? Messy and friends meet bee royalty and save the day.

25.title: Tiny Sandwiches
25.plot: Messy joins Zim and his friends on a mission inside a sandwich to photograph some atoms for Mayor Oki - Everyone say cheese.

26.title: Big Hearted Messy
26.plot: Messy, Zoe and Felix have to get Lofty's heart pumping.

27.title: Building Bridges
27.plot: Messy and his friends are joined by a group of robots to build a bridge to reach Billy Barnacle. Stan tall puts it to the test.

28.title: Cheesy Feet
28.plot: Messy thinks smelly socks and cheesy feet are brie-lliant! But when it's Lofty's feet that smell, it's a giant problem.

29.title: Colours
29.plot: Messy and friends are left feeling blue when the vacubots suck all the colour out of Okido! So they better get ready to fix it!

30.title: Habitat
30.plot: When the Cloudship malfunctions and soars off into Okido, it's up to Messy and friends to return it to its natural habitat.

31.title: Mayor Force One
31.plot: Messy gets to fly Mayor Oki's plane, but this is no easy jet and he crash lands in a tree - Luckily, robots fly to the rescue.

32.title: Vivienne Blows Her Top
32.plot: Messy and his friends have animals to save and eruptions to stop in Okido when Vivienne Volcano gets a rumbly tummy. Oh deary.

33.title: Fossil Puzzle
33.plot: In the real world Messy is bored of his dino-jigsaw. In Okido, his friends help him piece together a real prehistoric puzzle.

34.title: Funny Bones
34.plot: Mustard goes in search for help - Lofty has a broken finger. Messy and friends save the day and discover bones are amazing.

35.title: Messy Antics
35.plot: It's Mayor Oki's birthday picnic. Messy and friends get in trouble with Zam's shrinkasizer. Time to solve these Okido ant-ics.

36.title: Spider Messy
36.plot: Messy goes to Okido and helps his friends to mend Loopy Bridge but along the way Zim finds himself in a sticky situation.

37.title: Dizzy
37.plot: Messy and friends go on a rollercoaster adventure and figure out why Stan tall is in such a spin.

38.title: Me and My Shadow
38.plot: When Messy breaks the lighthouse things get shady - But without a shadow of a doubt, he and his friends save the day.

39.title: A Case of the Lightnings
39.plot: Messy and friends visits Fluff the cloud's family, and things heat up in flash when her brother Nimby gets the lightenings.

40.title: Okidoasis
40.plot: Messy's thirsty for an adventure, so he goes to Okido to help his friends solve the mystery of the dried up Oasis.

41.title: Messy Music
41.plot: Messy and friends must play the Okido concert. Music is instrumental, but then it's time for Okido to make some noise.

42.title: A Sock Too Far
42.plot: When Messy and his friends go camping with a robot who can do anything, there is a giant sized socksident.

43.title: Rumbly Tummy
43.plot: Messy's tummy is rumbling and so is Lofty the giant's. Luckily the gang are hungry to solve this scientific mystery though.

44.title: Rub A Dub Messy
44.plot: When Messy and friends discover how to catapult heavy things with a lever, farmyard animal bathtime commences with a splash.

45.title: Splish Splash Splosh
45.plot: Lofty's giant sneezes go a long way, so Messy and his friends must help to wash Okido clean of all the bad germs flying around.

46.title: Eye Spy
46.plot: Messy and friends search explore the forest with Tweedy, but when her eyesight fails luckily Zim, Zam and Zoom can lens a hand.

47.title: Snowflakes
47.plot: It's summer in Okido, but Messy wants to chill out in the snow, so he's lucky when the snowflakes come out to play.

48.title: Wiggly Worms
48.plot: When Mayor Oki's pumpkins aren't big enough Messy and his friends muck in and save the day. With the help of some wiggly worms.

49.title: Second Chances
49.plot: Messy helps his friends find Zoe's lost communicator, which has ended up in the recycling but luckily, Zim is magnetic.

50.title: Messy Races
50.plot: Messy and friends enter a race in Okido and the various vehicles speed off. But who has the power to win the mystery prize?

51.title: Giant Messy
51.plot: Messy and friends go to the funfair, but when the shrinkasizer comes out, they end up in a giant mess with mini Mini.

52.title: Tick Tock Messy
52.plot: Messy goes to Okido to play with Zim and Zam's new discovery. But will he and his friends get back from this adventure in time.

imdb.plot outline: OKIDO is a comedy adventure, science-educational series following a curious, adventure seeking and unruly monster called Messy as he finds the answers to everything a 3-5 year old child wants to know. Why do things fall down and not up? Where do echoes come from? Messy goes on incredible adventures with his two best friends, Zoe and Felix to find the answers. They are helped along the way by the bonkers science trio Zim, Zam and Zoom. Together they will fly to the moon, shrink to the size of atoms and fly on the back of a giant butterfly.
